After version 2:
Tested on the same 3 validation frames as last time and the predictions are visually much better, the model clearly learned a lot. But there's a catch: it's gotten so confident that it's now hallucinating rare classes like cyclists and motorcyclists where they don't actually exist in the scene.

Ran until ~400 epochs and sitting at 54-55% mIoU. The number looks okay but honestly it's misleading, common classes like road, buildings and vegetation are at 85%+ but rare classes are dragging the overall score down and more importantly aren't reliable in realistic scenarios.

Considering 2 options for now:
1. Add more rare class data, specifically sequences with more pedestrians, cyclists and motorcyclists
2. Remove/merge the classes we can't learn properly at this data size

epoch=450, epoch step=150, val step=150
val mIoU - 54-55% - hallucinating!!!!!!!!!
Going with option 1. Will get the data sorted and will work on it next week. 

